commit.message: Fix typos, make conch.ui.ansi.log private, and use camelCase
Add empty news fragment
Remove always-false version check when importing HTTP/2

Remove override of assertRegex()

Since the override now does nothing except calling the superclass
implementation, there is no need to keep it.

It could be argued that the docstring has value, but I think it's
more consistent to refer to the standard library documentation
instead, since that will be kept up-to-date. Also it is more
consistent since for example assertNotRegex() exists in the
standard library but is not overridden here.
Remove version check in assertRegex()

Remove uses of sys.exc_clear()

This no longer exists in Python 3.

Most of its calls were behind explicit version checks, except
a precautionary one in test_json. However, since the exception
will no longer be active after the 'except' block is exited,
there is no need to clear it explicitly anymore in Python 3.

Drop inline imports from ensureDeferred()

Since it is no longer conditional, there is no need to do the import
of iscoroutine() inline.

For the import of GeneratorType, there already was no need to do
the import inline and in fact other parts of this module access it
as 'types.GeneratorType'.
Remove always-true version check in ensureDeferred()

Update ignore pattern passed to check-manifest

The syntax of ignore patterns changed in check-manifest 0.42:
directories must now be ignored using 'name/**' instead of 'name*'.

I also removed 'twisted/topfiles' from the exclude list since that
directory no longer exists.
Add empty news fragment

Drop explicit inheritance from 'object' class

This was necessary in Python 2 to force new-style classes.
In Python 3, it's just noise.

Substitutions were done automatically with 'sed', except:
- twisted/words/xish/xpathparser.g was done by hand and
  xpathparser.py was re-generated from that
- twisted/test/test_plugin.py was done by hand
